.Dd June 26, 2026
.Dt VSGPTINFO 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm vsgptinfo
.Nd determines information about a GUID Partition Table (GPT) volume system
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm vsgptinfo
.Op Fl hvV
.Ar source
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm vsgptinfo
is a utility to determine information about a GUID Partition Table (GPT) \
volume system
.Pp
.Nm vsgptinfo
is part of the
.Nm libvsgpt
package.
.Nm libvsgpt
is a library to access the GUID Partition Table (GPT) volume system format
.Pp
.Ar source
is the source image.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl h
shows this help
.It Fl v
verbose output to stderr
.It Fl V
print version
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
None
.Sh FILES
None
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal
# vsgptinfo /dev/sda
vsgptinfo 20260626
.sp
GUID Partition Table (GPT) information:
	Disk identifier		: 2d522f96-53ad-4b0b-9271-689a8775f9a0
	Bytes per sector	: 512
	Number of partitions	: 1
.sp
Partition: 1
	Identifier		: f2f05925-ed66-427b-83f3-db2679ff29f1
	Type identifier		: 0fc63daf-8483-4772-8e79-3d69d8477de4
	Type			: 0x00 (Empty)
	Offset			: 1048576 (0x00100000)
	Size			: 65536
.sp
.Ed
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
Errors, verbose and debug output are printed to stderr when verbose output \
\-v is enabled.
Verbose and debug output are only printed when enabled at compilation.
